Regardless of numbers of digits, each record in our database has 14 fields separated with semicolons. Here's a sample record to describe the fields:

543145;MASTERCARD;U.S. BANK, N.A.;DEBIT;ENHANCED;UNITED STATES;US;USA;840;WWW.USBANK.COM;1-800-US BANKS;16;PERSONAL;Y

1. "543145" - BIN,
2. "MASTERCARD" - card brand,
3. "U.S. BANK, N.A." - issuing organization,
4. "DEBIT" - type of card (DEBIT, CREDIT, or CHARGE CARD),
5. "ENHANCED" - category of card,
6. "UNITED STATES" - issuing country ISO name,
7. "US" - issuing country ISO A2 code,
8. "USA" - issuing country ISO A3 code,
9. "840" - issuing country ISO number,
10. "WWW.USBANK.COM" - issuing organization website,
11. "1-800-US BANKS" - issuing organization phone number,
12. "16" - PAN length,
13. "PERSONAL" - PERSONAL or COMMERCIAL flag,
14. "Y" - regulated (Y) or unregulated (N) BIN.
